# Phase closeout playbook mode (requestable)

When the operator is **closing a phase** and preparing a **release**:

1. Open and follow **`docs/maintainers/playbooks/phase-closeout-and-release.md`** (playbook id `phase-closeout-and-release`). Prefer attaching that file (`@`) so steps stay in context.
2. Use **`docs/maintainers/AGENTS.md`** for source-of-truth order and **`docs/maintainers/AGENT-CLI-MAP.md`** for every **`workspace-kit run`** line that mutates kit-owned state.
3. **Policy:** sensitive `workspace-kit run` commands require JSON **`policyApproval`** in the third CLI argument; `config` / `init` / `upgrade` use env approval per **`docs/maintainers/POLICY-APPROVAL.md`**. Chat-only approval does not satisfy policy.
4. **Human gate:** do not publish or run release automation until explicit human approval — see **`docs/maintainers/RELEASING.md`**.
5. After publish, use the playbook’s **§7 Phase delivery summary** for the final user-facing wrap-up (evidence-backed counts; not JSON **`responseTemplateId`** on **`wk run`**).

Invocation options and limits of auto-loading: **`docs/maintainers/runbooks/agent-playbooks.md`**.

This rule does **not** override **`maintainer-delivery-loop.mdc`** or **`workspace-kit-cli-execution.mdc`**; it points at the same playbook and policy surfaces.
